<font color="#FF0000">ON &quot;CANNON FODDER&quot;</font><br>
<tt>Sat Dec 14 19:49:28 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Phill Coleman, an African-American vet who served a full tour in Vietnam as an Army communications/intelligence specialist, is an articulate chronologer. His &quot;Cannon Fodder&quot; (located at http://members.aol.com/veterans/cf.htm) pulls no punches about the reasons for America's failed mission in Vietnam. Rarely do black vets devote so little discussion on race relations in Vietnam. Coleman puts the racial issue in the same category as others that helped to undermine GI relations and diminish their productivity... a tool used by North Vietnamese like drugs, prostitution and other problems that stymied the US. A revelational book! I think Cannon Fodder is a historical treasure on the Vietnam War.
